":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Lord Thomas Peyvre 4th Baron Peyvre was born in 1352, in Toddington, Bedfordshire, England, his father, Sir Nicholas Peyvre 3rd Baron Peyvre, was 34 and his mother, Margaret d'Arden, was 34. He married Lady Margaret Loring in 1368, in Chalgrave, Bedfordshire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died on 22 September 1429, in his hometown, at the age of 77."},"et":{"1352–22 September 1429":"1352–22. september 1429","1352–1429":"1352–1429","1356–1449":"1356–1449","1382–1409":"1382–1409","1318–1361":"1318–1361","1318–1379":"1318–1379","1352":"1352","22 September 1429":"22. september 1429","1361":"1361","1382":"1382","13 September 1361":"13. september 1361","1368":"1368","1379":"1379","1356":"1356","1409":"1409","26 July 1409":"26. juuli 1409","1429":"1429","1318":"1318","1449":"1449","Toddington, Bedfordshire, England":"Toddington, Bedfordshire, England","Staffordshire, England":"Staffordshire, England","Chalgrave, Bedfordshire, England":"Chalgrave, Bedfordshire, England","Castle Cary, Somerset, England":"Castle Cary, Somerset, England"},"fi":{"1352–22 September 1429":"1352–22. syyskuuta 1429","1352–1429":"1352–1429","1356–1449":"1356–1449","1382–1409":"1382–1409","1318–1361":"1318–1361","1318–1379":"1318–1379","1352":"1352","22 September 1429":"22. syyskuuta 1429","1361":"1361","1382":"1382","13 September 1361":"13. syyskuuta 1361","1368":"1368","1379":"1379","1356":"1356","1409":"1409","26 July 1409":"26. heinäkuuta 1409","1429":"1429","1318":"1318","1449":"1449","Toddington, Bedfordshire, England":"Toddi